article.headline: Old Dominion 74, South Carolina St. 57
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Valdas Vasylius scored 20 points and Drew Williamson added 15 to lead Old Dominion to a 74-57 win over South Carolina State on Saturday night. The Monarchs (7-3) shot a season-high 54.2 percent from the field and 42.9 percent from beyond the arc. They outrebounded the Bulldogs 31-22. After ODU took a 33-26 halftime lead, the Bulldogs (2-7) cut it to three before the Monarchs used a 16-0 run led by Vasylius and Williamson to lead by 19. Julius Carter led the Bulldogs with 12 points on 6-of-7 shooting and six rebounds. Brian Henderson added 12 for the Monarchs.
